	(text "RGB termination / voltage divider resistors values\nare depending on monitor jungle (chroma/deflection) IC. \n\nFor jungle ICs with 0.7Vpp RGB inputs (like TDA8366):\nR1, R2, R3: 0 Ohm,\nR6, R7, R8: 75 Ohm.\n\nFor jungle ICs with 0.5Vpp RGB inputs (like TA1276AN):\nR1, R2, R3: 30 Ohm,\nR6, R7, R8: 75 Ohm.\nAttenuation / divider resistors R1, R2, R3 can be changed to 24 Ohm,\nand termination resistors R6, R7, R8 to 51 Ohm for \"proper\" 75 Ohm termination."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 151.638 33.782 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "307923aa-e8a6-4733-8a5a-25d2ce4ab937")
	)
	(text "Blanking voltage divider / pulldown resistors values\nare depends on jungle IC requirements.\nFor 3V inputs use R9=1K/1.2K, R10=2.3K/2.8K, and so on.\nSome ICs require pulldown R10=10\\~50K.\nR12 can be omitted but R9=120R\\~180R is recommended to limit current."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 125.73 59.436 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "b80fbf6e-1d2f-4f4f-aeee-094946261143")
	)
